sentences: Whitcomb was Director of Bands at FSU from 1953 to 1970.
He became the coordinator of the FSU music education program in 1971.
Prior to arriving at FSU, Whitcomb was at Ohio State University in 1937.
He became the conductor of both the Concert Band and the Marching Band in 1940 and served as the Director from 1939-43 and 1946-51, taking time off for military service during World War II.
He was named the first Alumni Professor of the year at FSU in 1968, and was named as one of the ten most outstanding music directors in the US by School Musician magazine in 1972.
